File: Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga. JOHANNESBURG - Several education unions are accusing the Basic Education Department of not properly consulting with them. The unions say the department is conducting itself on the consultations causing a trust deficit. They are also denying that they have been properly consulted and have agreed on the reopening plan. READ: Reopening of schools in question Unions have cautioned against rushing teachers and pupils back to school. They say the agreed date for the return of management teams is the 18th of June but the department wants schooling to resume at the beginning of next month. Minister of Basic Education Angie Motshekga is expected to address the nation on the possible timeline for reopening schools on Thursday. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.